input.issue_body:
We noticed the following behavior changes between 1.5.1 and 1.5.2+ (1.5.2 and 1.5.3) related to middleware handlers.
- Middleware handlers got instantiated twice in 1.5.2+. It's once in 1.5.1.
- Middleware handlers got invoked twice for URLs routed to NotFound handlers in 1.5.2+. It's once in 1.5.1.

Example code:
```
package main

import (
	"fmt"
	"net/http"

	"github.com/go-chi/chi"
)

func main() {
	r := chi.NewRouter()

	r.Use(func(next http.Handler) http.Handler {
		fmt.Println("Instantiating test middleware...")
		return http.HandlerFunc(func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {
			fmt.Println(r.URL.Path, "going through middleware...")
			next.ServeHTTP(w, r)
		})
	})

	r.NotFound(func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {
		w.WriteHeader(404)
		w.Write([]byte("Resource not found\n"))
	})

	r.Get("/hello", func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {
		w.WriteHeader(200)
		w.Write([]byte("Hello world!\n"))
	})

	svr := &http.Server{
		Addr:    ":6060",
		Handler: r,
	}

	fmt.Println("Starting server...")
	if err := svr.ListenAndServe(); err != nil && err != http.ErrServerClosed {
		fmt.Println("Server stopped with error:", err)
	} else {
		fmt.Println("Server stopped normally")
	}
}
```

Output after one `GET /hello` and one `GET /nihao` requests in 1.5.2+:
```
Instantiating test middleware...
Instantiating test middleware...
Starting server...
/hello going through middleware...
/nihao going through middleware...
/nihao going through middleware...
```

Output of the same case in 1.5.1:
```
Instantiating test middleware...
Starting server...
/hello going through middleware...
/nihao going through middleware...
```

